Quote: [O]f the many different ways of making such couches perhaps the most comfortable and driest is the plan of laying small saplings side by side, with the ends raised on cross pieces a few inches from the ground, and strewing such a platform with quantities of the fronds of piupiu - a peculiarly dry fern.
